Data Science Consultant (Internship)

AgReliant Genetics – Agrotechnology Firm, Westfield, IN

January 2025 - Present

  • Conducted supply chain evaluations using Python, R, and Snowflake to identify inefficiencies in shipment consolidation and warehouse mapping, improving fulfillment accuracy and reducing excess deliveries.
  • Designed KPIs in Tableau to track delivery frequency, warehouse utilization, and logistics costs, enabling data-driven decision-making and better supply-sales alignment.
  • Built a network flow optimization model using XGBoost, Random Forest, Solver, and Python PuLP to manage seasonal demand and customer-to-warehouse allocation.
  • Automated key workflows and integrated risk models to enhance operational efficiency and system performance.

Junior Supply Chain Analyst

Tayaba Welfare International Association – Social Enterprise, Lahore, Pakistan

January 2023 - April 2024

  • Applied Apache Spark for EDA to uncover procurement patterns, improve data quality, and enable more accurate aid distribution strategies.
  • Used SAS-EM for regression modeling and time-series forecasting to streamline flood-relief distribution routes, supporting the deployment of 4,000+ H2O Wheels.
  • Built Excel-based stochastic optimization models to ensure consistent resource allocation for 8,000 wheels across varying terrains and constraints.
  • Worked closely with cross-functional teams to co-develop scalable solutions and maintain rigorous documentation standards.

Business Analyst

DSME Global Links – Software Firm, Amsterdam, Netherlands

February 2022 - December 2022

  • Leveraged Python and LLM modeling to analyze user engagement, using Databricks and statistical modeling to generate insights that led to a 12% growth increase.
  • Built Tableau dashboards to track KPIs for 20+ clients, integrating transaction data and agile analytics to enhance decision-making.
  • Conducted market segmentation using SQL and Excel, delivering accurate financial insights and maintaining reporting consistency on Looker Studio.
  • Developed scalable prototypes and contributed to cross-functional solutions aligned with product and business goals.
